The article discusses President Biden's recognition of the Tulsa race massacre and his concerns about the assault on voting rights in the United States. He calls for a redoubling of efforts to expand voting rights and overcome the surge in efforts to undermine the right to vote through anti-voter laws. The President believes that these voter suppression laws are meant to attack Americans' constitutional rights, especially people of color. He has taken unprecedented action to advance voting rights and recently named Vice President Harris to lead a campaign on this issue. The article also mentions the actions the administration has taken on voting rights since taking office, including doubling the staff of the Department of Justice's Civil Rights Division for protecting the right to vote.